-- Russian Apple Retailer Plans to Sell Stake, Kommersant Says
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-09-27T04:31:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/russian-apple-retailer-plans-to-sell-stake-kommersant-says.html
re:Store Retail Group , an official
seller of  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  products with 94 stores in Russia and
 Europe , plans to sell a stake,  Kommersant  reported, citing an
unidentified person in banking.  The company, valued at $210 million to $280 million, is
looking for a financial consultant for the sale, the newspaper
said. Georgiy Lens, the owner and president of Lanit Group, a
holding of Internet technology companies including re:Store,
said that if the owners are offered a good price, they will sell
a stake, Kommersant reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
